<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="text-align: left;"><b><hr /><br /></b></div><div style="text-align: left;"><b>The state of mind: Feelings</b></div><div><br /></div><div><ol start="1"><li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Feeling of a guilt</span></li></ol></div><div>Its like when you loose your charges.<br /></div><div><ol start="2"><li><span style="font-weight: bold;">Feeling of not having any control of anything.</span></li></ol></div><div>…Having a problem letting go.</div><div><hr /><br /></div><div>   <span style="font-weight: bold;"> </span><span style="font-weight: bold;">Why wonderfull night thougts and ideas are no longer wonderful?</span></div><div> Its about middle of the night and the wondefull thoughts are keep coming. New ideas about the things</div><div>and events. It feels so real and so great,  no way for me to go to sleep. A lot of fantastic imagination and hope.</div><div>When I woke up next day, for some reason those thoughts and idea seem to me totally unrealistic and stupid.</div><div>The worst of all, how many time I have done the same thing over and over again?</div><div><br /></div><div><br /></div><div>    <b>How to get out from the loop of thoughts?</b><br /></div><div><span>What I mean by the “loop of thoughts”?</span></div><div><span><br /></span></div><div> </div><div><br /></div></en-note>